  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 2110 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Peel @Carrots{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Halve @Yellow Onion{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped). Core and finely chop @Roma Tomato{1}(cored and finely chopped).

Place @Butter{1 1/2%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until just soft, about ~{10%seconds} (do not melt). Stir in @Italian Seasoning{1/4%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{3%teaspoon} in a medium #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian Chicken Sausage{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, about ~{5%minutes}. Add a large drizzle of olive oil, then stir in carrot, onion, and a large pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, about ~{5%minutes}.

Stir remaining @Italian Seasoning{3/4%tsp} into pot. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in tomato and @Tomato Paste{1 1/2%ounce}. Cook, stirring, until well combined, about ~{1%minute}. Stir in @Farro{1/2%cup}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2}, a few big pinches of salt, and @water{3%cups}. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium low. Simmer ~{10%minutes}, then uncover pot and simmer until farro is tender, about ~{5%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, halve @Ciabatta Bread{1} (as if you were making a sandwich). Toast in #toaster{} or #toaster oven{} until golden. Spread with herb butter, then halve toasts diagonally.

Stir half the @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup} into soup. Season soup with salt and pepper to taste. Divide between bowls, then garnish with remaining Parmesan. Serve with toasts on the side.

> During this time of year, we crave dinners that are hearty, rustic, and soul-warming. This soup checks all of those boxes with a tomatoey broth, Italian chicken sausage, aromatic herbs, and farro - an ancient grain with a wholesome, nutty flavor.

> No soup is complete without some bread for dunking - that's why we add ciabatta toasts spread with herb butter.